# GTM Multi-Analytics Integration Rules

Full documentation: `docs/gtm-skill/plan.md`

## Naming conventions
- DLV variables: `DLV - property_name`
- Triggers: `PLATFORM - Event_Name`
- Tags: `PLATFORM - Event_Name`
- SDK Loader tags: `PLATFORM - SDK Loader`
- Platform abbreviations: GA4, CT, MP, CL, GADS
- dataLayer keys: always snake_case

## pushEvent utility
```typescript
// lib/gtm.ts
export const pushEvent = (event: string, params?: Record<string, unknown>) => {
  if (typeof window === 'undefined') return
  window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []
  window.dataLayer.push({ event, ...params })
}
```

## Critical rules
- Always call pushEvent AFTER async actions succeed, never on click
- dataLayer keys must match GTM DLV names exactly — case-sensitive
- Trigger event names must match pushEvent calls exactly — case-sensitive
- SDK Loader tags: All Pages trigger, no filters, priority 10, type="text/javascript"
- Never commit service account JSON or .env to git
- Always DRY_RUN=true before applying scripts
- Always Submit/Publish GTM after changes — Preview uses draft, not live

